gaffer.function.simple.aggregate

Class NumericAggregateFunction

  • java.lang.Object
    • gaffer.function.ConsumerFunction
      • gaffer.function.ConsumerProducerFunction
        • gaffer.function.AggregateFunction
          • gaffer.function.SimpleAggregateFunction<Number>
            • gaffer.function.simple.aggregate.NumericAggregateFunction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Function, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Max, Min, Product, Sum

    public abstract class NumericAggregateFunction
extends SimpleAggregateFunction<Number>
    An NumericAggregateFunction is a SimpleAggregateFunction that takes in Numbers of the same type and processes the number in some way. To implement this class just implement the init methods and aggregate methods for the different number types. If you know the type of number that will be used then this can be set by calling setMode(NumberType), otherwise it will be automatically set for you using the class of the first number passed in.
